SIMPLE: fulguration
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fulguration
<hw>Ful"gu*ra`tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fulguratio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>fulguration</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of lightening.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Donne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Assaying)</fld> <def>The sudden brightening of a
fused globule of gold or silver, when the last film of the oxide of lead
or copper leaves its surface; -- also called
<altname>blick</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A phenomenon called, by the old chemists,
<qex>fulguration</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Ure.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fulgurite</ent>⟦br⟧
